            <title>[GROOVY-7461] Groovy doesn&apos;t write BOM if UTF-16 alias is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7461</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;newWriter(charset, append)&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;File.append(text, charset)&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;File.write(text, charset)&lt;/tt&gt; methods all don&apos;t write the UTF-16 BOM if an alias for UTF-16 is used.  For example, if the &quot;UTF_16LE&quot; alias for &quot;UTF-16LE&quot; is used, no BOM is written even though a BOM is written for the canonical name.  This is because &lt;tt&gt;writeUTF16BomIfRequired(charset, stream)&lt;/tt&gt; only checks for the canonical name, and not any aliases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
